HEADWORD: Glucina
<hw>Glu*ci"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>glycine</ets>, <ets>glucine</ets>. So called because it forms sweet
salts. See <er>Glucinum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white or
gray tasteless powder, the oxide of the element glucinum; -- formerly
called <xex>glucine</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glucinic</ent>⟦br⟧
